am Airport]])\n* 2502 ([[Hamilton, Leicestershire|Hamilton]])\n}}\n\n=== Trent Wing ===\n;Wing HQ [[RAF Digby]]\n{{columns-list|colwidth=20em|\n* XVII - 17 ([[Coningsby]])\n* 47F ([[Grantham]])\n* 119 ([[Scunthorpe]])\n* 140 ([[Matlock, Derbyshire|Matlock]])\n* 141 ([[Boston, Lincolnshire|Boston]])\n* 195 ([[Grimsby]])\n* 203 ([[Gainsborough, Lincolnshire|Gainsborough]])\n* 204 (City of [[Lincoln, England|Lincoln]])\n* 303 ([[Worksop]])\n* 331 ([[Chesterfield]])\n* 384 ([[Mansfield]])\n* 620 ([[Duffield, Derbyshire|Derwent Valley]])\n* 866 ([[Immingham]])\n* 1073 ([[Skegness]])\n* 1082 ([[Brimington]] & District)\n* 1208 ([[Warsop]])\n* 1228 ([[Louth, Lincolnshire|Louth]])\n*:1228DF ([[Mablethorpe]])\n* 1237 ([[North Hykeham]])\n* 1260 ([[Newark-on-Trent|Newark]] & District)\n* 1265 ([[Horncastle, Lincolnshire|Horncastle]])\n* 1300 ([[Sutton-in-Ashfield]])\n* 1401 ([[Alfreton]] & [[Ripley, Derbyshire|Ripley]])\n* 1403 ([[Retford]])\n* 1803 ([[Hucknall]])\n* 1890 ([[Dronfield]])\n* 2000 ([[Eckington, Derbyshire|Eckington]])\n* 2160 ([[Sleaford]])\n* 2222 ([[Brigg]])\n* 2292 ([[Market Rasen]])\n* 2326 ([[Clay Cross]])\n}}\n\n=== Warwickshire & Birmingham Wing ===\n;Wing HQ Coventry (Army Reserve Centre Canley)\n{{columns-list|colwidth=20em|\n* 8F (1st City of [[Coventry]])\n* 29F ([[Rugby, Warwickshire|Rugby]])\n* 84 ([[Coventry Airport]])\n* 121 ([[Nuneaton]])\n* 163 ([[Canley|Coventry Phoenix]])\n* 165 ([[Castle Bromwich]])\n* 194 ([[Birmingham Small Arms Company|BSA]] and City of [[Birmingham]])\n* 198 ([[Hinckley]])\n* 479 ([[Rubery]])\n* 480 ([[Studley, Warwickshire|Studley]])\n* 485 ([[Harborne]] & [[Quinton, Birmingham|Quinton]])\n* 487 ([[Kingstanding]] & [[Perry Barr]])\n* 489 ([[Acocks Green]] & [[Olton]])\n* 491 (City of [[Birmingham]]) Disbanded/merged with 194?\n* 492 ([[Solihull]])\n*: 492DF ([[St Paul's School for Girls|St Pauls]])\n* 493 ([[Kings Heath]] & [[Moseley]])\n* 495 ([[Sutton Coldfield]])\n* 496 ([[Kenilworth]] and [[Balsall Common]])\n* 497 