rynamman]]) (formerly 1455, 2475DF and 1358DF) Disbanded\n* 360 ([[Llwchwr]])\n* 499 ([[Port Talbot]])\n* 561 (Ardwyn, [[Aberystwyth]] & District)\n* 621 ([[Carmarthen]])\n* 631 ([[Maesteg]]) Disbanded\n* 948 ([[Haverfordwest]] and City of [[St Davids]])\n* 1054 ([[Llanelli]])\n* 1092 ([[Bridgend]])\n* 1284 ([[Tenby]])\n* 1358 ([[Pontardawe]])\n* 1429 ([[Cardigan, Ceredigion|Cardigan]] & [[Aberporth]])\n* 1574 ([[Pembroke, Pembrokeshire|Pembroke]])\n* 1998 ([[West Cross]])\n* 2117 ([[Kenfig Hill]])\n* 2227 (Mid Gwendraeth) Disbanded\n* 2318 ([[Aberkenfig]])\n* 2347 ([[Porthcawl]])\n* 2420 ([[Whitland]] & District)\n* 2426 ([[Pencoed]] & District)\n* 2475 ([[Ammanford]])\n}}\n\n== Scotland & Northern Ireland Region ==\n\n;Region HQ [[Leuchars Station]]\n\n=== Highland Wing ===\n;Wing HQ [[RAF Lossiemouth]], Moray\n{{columns-list|colwidth=20em|\n* 52 ([[Aviemore]])\n* 161 (1st Highland)\n*:161DF ([[Ullapool]])\n* 379 (County of [[Ross, Scotland|Ross]])\n* 423 ([[Elgin, Moray|Elgin]])\n*:423DF ([[Strathspey, Scotland|Speyside]])\n* 446 ([[Forres]])\n* 832 ([[Wester Ross]])\n* 1068 ([[Nairn]])\n* 1285 ([[Caithness]])\n* 1730 ([[Lochaber]])\n* 1731 ([[Isle of Lewis]])\n* 1769 ([[Thurso]] & District)\n*:1769DF ([[Orkney]])\n* 2405 ([[Dingwall]])\n* 2521 ([[Oban]] High School)\n}}\n\n=== North East Scotland Wing ===\n;Wing HQ [[Gordon Barracks]], Aberdeen\n{{columns-list|colwidth=20em|\n* 102 ([[Aberdeen Airport]])\n* 107 ([[Aberdeen]])\n* 865 ([[Portlethen]])\n* 875 ([[Westhill, Aberdeenshire|Westhill]])\n* 877 ([[Inverurie]])\n* 1295 ([[Peterhead]])\n* 1296 ([[Turriff]])\n* 1297 ([[Stonehaven]])\n* 1298 ([[Huntly]])\n* 1383 ([[Fraserburgh]])\n* 1990 ([[Ellon, Aberdeenshire|Ellon]])\n* 2231 ([[Forfar]])\n* 2288 ([[Montrose, Angus|Montrose]])\n* 2365 ([[Brechin]])\n* 2367 ([[Banchory]])\n* 2422 ([[Arbroath]])\n* 2449 ([[Carnoustie]])\n* 2489 ([[Bridge of Don]])\n}}\n\n=== South East Scotland Wing ===\n;Wing HQ [[Leuchars Station]]\n{{columns-list|colwidth=20em|\n* 38F ([[Perth, Scotland|Perth]])\n* 132 ([[North Berwick]])\n* 142 ([[Trinity, Edinburgh|Trinity]])\n* 287 ([[Stenhouse, Edinburgh|Stenhouse]])\n* 297 ([[Musselburgh]])\n* 383 ([[Alloa]])\n* 439 ([[Linlithgow]])\n* 571 ([[Cupar]])\n* 775 ([[Burntisland]])\n* 859 ([[Dalgety Bay]])\n* 869 ([[Penicuik]])\n* 870 ([[Dreghorn]])\n*:870DF ([[Gilmerton]])\n* 1007 ([[Duns]])\n* 1019 (City of [[Stirling]])\n* 1143 (8th Edinburgh) aka 1143 ([[Portobello, Edinburgh|Portobello]]) Sqn\n* 1145 ([[Dunfermline]])\n*:1145DF ([[Kinross]])\n* 1192 ([[Kirkcaldy]])\n* 1232 (City of [[Dundee]])\n* 1370 ([[Leven, Fife|Leven]])\n* 1716 ([[Roxburgh]])\n*:1716DF ([[Kelso, Scottish Borders|Kelso]])\n* 1739 (2nd [[Midlothian]])\n* 1743 ([[Crieff]])\n* 1756 ([[Broxburn, West Lothian|Broxburn]])\n* 2163 ([[Auchtermuchty]])\n* 2180 ([[Galashiels]])\n* 2284 ([[Dunblane]])\n* 2311 ([[Glenrothes]])\n* 2345 ([[Leuchars]])\n* 2435 ([[St Andrews]])\n* 2450 ([[Dundee]])\n* 2463 ([[Currie]] & [[Balerno]])\n* 2466 ([[Loanhead]])\n* 2519 ([[Strathmore, Angus|Strathmore]])\n* 2535 ([[Livingston, West Lothian|Livingston]])\n}}\n\n=== West Scotland & Northern Ireland Wing ===\n;Wing HQ Paisley Cadet Centre\n{{columns-list|colwidth=20em|\n;West Scottish Squadrons\n* 32F (1st Scottish)\n* 49F ([[Greenock]] ([[MacRobert baronets|MacRoberts Reply]]))\n* 62 (2nd [[Glasgow]])\n* 122 (5th [[Glasgow]])\n* 137 ([[Ayr]] & [[Prestwick]])\n* 327 ([[Kilmarnock]])\n* 396 ([[Paisley, Renfrewshire|Paisley]])\n* 449 ([[Lanark]])\n* 470 ([[Falkirk]])\n* 498 ([[Wishaw]])\n* 867 ([[Denny, Falkirk|Denny]])\n* 1001 ([[Monklands (district)|Monklands]])\n* 1089 (7th [[Glasgow]])\n* 1138 ([[Ardrossan]])\n* 1153 (2nd [[Dumfries]]shire)\n* 1195 ([[Irvine, North Ayrshire|Irvine]])\n* 1271 ([[Bathgate]])\n* 1333 ([[Grangemouth]] [[Spitfire]])\n* 1371 ([[Girvan]])\n* 1701 ([[Johnstone]])\n* 1740 ([[Clydebank]])\n* 1777 ([[Dumbarton]] [[Blackburn Aircraft|Blackburn]])\n* 2166 ([[Hamilton, South Lanarkshire|Hamilton]])\n* 2175 ([[Hillington, Scotland|Rolls-Royce]])\n* 2296 ([[Dunoon]])\n* 2329 ([[Castle Douglas]])\n* 2414 ([[East Kilbride]])\n* 2452 ([[Shawlands Academy]])\n* 2496 ([[Cumbernauld]])\n}}\n;Northern Irish Squadrons\n* 72 (Omagh)\n* 806 (Larne)\n* 814 ([[Portadown College]])\n* 817 (Lisburn)\n* 825 (Bangor)\n* 833 (Antrim)\n* 1136 (South Belfast)\n* 1137 (East Belfast)\n* 1919 (Newtownabbey)\n* 2004 (Ballynahinch)\n* 2062 (Carrickfergus)\n* 2178 (Holywood)\n* 2241 ([[Regent House School]])\n* 2349 (Ballymena)\n* 2350 (Coleraine)\n\n== See also ==\n*[[List of squadrons in the New Zealand Air Training Corps|List of squadrons in the New Zealand ATC]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|http://www.raf.mod.uk/aircadets/|Air Cadets official website}}\n* [http://www.raf.mod.uk/aircadets/find-a-squadron// Air Cadets - Find a squadron]\n* [http://www.air-cadets-squadron-finder.org/ Air Cadets (ATC) Squadron Finder] - a searchable list of all ATC Squadrons by location and postcode providing Squadron and Wing contact details\n* {{curlie|Regional/Europe/United_Kingdom/Government/Defence/Cadets/Air_Training_Corps|Air Training Corps}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Air Training Corps Squadrons}}\n[[Category:Lists of Royal Air Force units and formations|ATC]]\n[[Category:Air Training Corps]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=December 2016}}\n{{Expand list|date=September 2010}}\n\nThe [[Air Training Corps]] (ATC) is a cadet organisation based in the [[United Kingdom]]. It is a voluntary youth group which is part of the [[Royal Air Force Air Cadets]]. The ATC is largely composed of individual units known as [[Squadron (aviation)|squadrons]]. These squadrons are organised into several different ''Wings'', which in turn are organised into six different ''Regions''. Together the ''Regions'' make up the ''Corps''.\n\nHeadquarters Air Cadets (HQAC) is located at [[Royal Air Force College Cranwell]], [[Lincolnshire]] and headed by [[Commandant Air Cadets]] Air Commodore [[Dawn McCafferty]].\n\n{{TOC right|limit=2}}\n\n== Founder Squadrons and Detached Flights ==\nThe first 50 squadrons formed have their squadron numbers followed by an F to show they are \"founder\" squadrons (e.g. No 45F(Worthing) Squadron). Only 30 are still in existence, as the other 20 have disbanded over time. Founder Squadrons that have reformed after being disbanded do not retain the F status.\n\nIn towns not large enough to sustain a squadron of 30 cadets, or as a supplement to an existing squadron in a larger town or city, a Detached Flight may be formed. This operates much like any other unit, but is technically a component part of a nearby larger squadron. There are currently approximately 48 Detached Flights, denoted by the letters \"DF\" after a squadron number. \n<!--\n* \n* NOTES TO EDITORS:\n* When adding squadrons to the list, please keep the lists sorted in numerical order!\n* Please do not add links to squadron websites.\n* \n-->\n\n== Central & East Region ==\n;Region HQ [[RAF Wyton]]\n\n=== Bedfordshire & Cambridgeshire Wing ===\n\n;Wing HQ RAF Wyton\n\n{{columns-list|colwidth=20em|\n* 10F ([[Luton]])\n* 22 ([[Sandy, Bedfordshire|Sandy]])\n* 51 ([[Orton, Peterborough|Orton]])\n* 73 ([[Huntingdon]])\n* 104 (City of [[Cambridge]])\n* 105 ([[Cambourne]])\n* 115 ([[Peterborough]])\n* 134 ([[Bedford]])\n* 207 ([[Cranfield]])\n* 272 ([[Wisbech]])\n* 460 ([[Dunstable]])\n* 511 ([[Ramsey, Cambridgeshire|Ramsey]])\n* 1003 ([[Leighton Buzzard]])\n* 1094 ([[Ely, Cambridgeshire|Ely]])\n* 1220 ([[March, Cambridgeshire|March]])\n* 1406 ([[Spalding, Lincolnshire|Spalding]])\n* 1451 ([[Haverhill, Suffolk|Haverhill]])\n* 1985 ([[Flitwick]])\n* 2065 ([[Biggleswade]])\n* 2331 ([[St Ives, Cambridgeshire|St Ives]])\n* 2417 ([[Newmarket, Suffolk|Newmarket]])\n* 2430 ([[Holbeach]])\n* 2461 ([[Sawston]])\n* 2462 ([[Oakley, Bedfordshire|Oakley]])\n* 2465 ([[Luton]] [[Icknield High School|Icknield]])